      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "n34ymJn6ftbtigEf4sn2L"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0G",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 255439004,
      "version": 1469,
      "versionNonce": 348715908,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774500081841,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. Fed Funds Rate (FFR)\n\nThe interest rate banks charge\neach other for overnight loans. The Fed\nsets a target range (e.g. 5.25% -\n5.50%). The Fed nudges market rates\ninto the window via Open Market\nOperations (OMO), Interest on Reserve\nBalances (IORB) and Overnight Reverse\nRepos (ON RRP).\n\nRAISE rate\n- credit gets expensive\n- slows economy\n- fights inflation\n\nLOWER rate\n- credit gets cheap\n- stimulates economy\n- fights unemployment",
      "fontSize": 21.79627462186006,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. Fed Funds Rate (FFR)\n\nThe interest rate banks charge\neach other for overnight loans. The Fed sets a target range (e.g. 5.25% - 5.50%). The Fed nudges market rates into the window via Open Market Operations (OMO), Interest on Reserve Balances (IORB) and Overnight Reverse Repos (ON RRP).\n\nRAISE rate\n- credit gets expensive\n- slows economy\n- fights inflation\n\nLOWER rate\n- credit gets cheap\n- stimulates economy\n- fights unemployment",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
