    {
      "id": "Ig4l4btvono86K9Z3cITl",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 271.94089833003636,
      "y": 876.1577492511702,
      "width": 460.3497326121356,
      "height": 537.5335254266248,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "wNkMBmAxQ0yaseeIl-dzV"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0J",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 527048356,
      "version": 1065,
      "versionNonce": 1009900804,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774499000245,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "2. Open Market Operations\n\nBuying/selling Treasury securities to\nmanage short-term rates. Primarily\nshort-term U.S. Treasuries (T-bills). The\nNY Fed's trading desk executes these\ndaily.\n\nBUY bonds\n- injects cash into banking system\n- higher demand for bonds\n- bond prices rise, bond yields fall\n- rates fall\n\nSELL bonds\n- pulls cash out of banking system\n- higher supply of bonds\n- bond prices fall, bond yields rise\n- rates rise",
      "fontSize": 22.63299054427894,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "2. Open Market Operations\n\nBuying/selling Treasury securities to manage short-term rates. Primarily short-term U.S. Treasuries (T-bills). The NY Fed's trading desk executes these daily.\n\nBUY bonds\n- injects cash into banking system\n- higher demand for bonds\n- bond prices rise, bond yields fall\n- rates fall\n\nSELL bonds\n- pulls cash out of banking system\n- higher supply of bonds\n- bond prices fall, bond yields rise\n- rates rise",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
