    {
      "id": "OyQtXwnXTicM-m97S6UQl",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 531.3155291755327,
      "y": 869.9190722497109,
      "width": 409.3393982634118,
      "height": 494.74399415568234,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "2VAYkopfZsiajSsJlRp2f"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0K",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1136981028,
      "version": 1130,
      "versionNonce": 530622524,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774499072846,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "2. Quantitative Easing / Tightening\n\nLarge-scale asset purchases (QE) or\nbalance sheet reduction (QT). A non-\nstandard tool, used when rates are\nalready near zero and more stimulus is\nneeded. Used notably in 2008 (GFC)\nand 2020 (COVID).\n\nQE\n- buy long-term bonds\n- lower long-term rates\n- stimulate borrowing & investment\n\nQT\n- let bonds mature / sell\n- reduce money supply\n- tighten financial conditions",
      "fontSize": 21.98862196247477,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "2. Quantitative Easing / Tightening\n\nLarge-scale asset purchases (QE) or balance sheet reduction (QT). A non-standard tool, used when rates are already near zero and more stimulus is needed. Used notably in 2008 (GFC) and 2020 (COVID).\n\nQE\n- buy long-term bonds\n- lower long-term rates\n- stimulate borrowing & investment\n\nQT\n- let bonds mature / sell\n- reduce money supply\n- tighten financial conditions",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
