      "updated": 1774499355197,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "C) Overnight Reverse Repos\n\n",
      "fontSize": 22.63299054427894,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "C) Overnight Reverse Repos\n\n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "INh49WuMDN8EO7hVlULdr",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 1531.3251235256314,
      "y": 879.5472556543548,
      "width": 376.47097593846007,
      "height": 419.24202058072996,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#846358",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "4mJ2vvtsJq1U6I_9xmmA0",
        "P1vscvoACG5iCgGEnvgQz"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1R",
      "roundness": {
        "type": 3
      },
      "seed": 1260003004,
      "version": 1891,
      "versionNonce": 2068776813,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776141472985,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false
    },
    {
      "id": "Gtwn9aD7PFZ7vyjiU-3hx",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1553.084563995431,
      "y": 899.298588508817,
      "width": 323.8573385460723,
      "height": 378.1563550306818,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#846358",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "4mJ2vvtsJq1U6I_9xmmA0",
        "P1vscvoACG5iCgGEnvgQz"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1S",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1549723452,
      "version": 2170,
      "versionNonce": 204837325,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776141472985,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "A) Open Market Operations (OMO)\n\nBuying/selling Treasury securities to\nmanage short-term rates. Primarily\nshort-term U.S. Treasuries (T-bills). The\nNY Fed's trading desk executes these\ndaily.\n\nBUY bonds\n- injects cash into banking system\n- higher demand for bonds\n- bond prices rise, bond yields fall\n- rates fall\n\nSELL bonds\n- pulls cash out of banking system\n- higher supply of bonds\n- bond prices fall, bond yields rise\n- rates rise",
      "fontSize": 15.922372843397131,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "A) Open Market Operations (OMO)\n\nBuying/selling Treasury securities to manage short-term rates. Primarily short-term U.S. Treasuries (T-bills). The NY Fed's trading desk executes these daily.\n\nBUY bonds\n- injects cash into banking system\n- higher demand for bonds\n- bond prices rise, bond yields fall\n- rates fall\n\nSELL bonds\n- pulls cash out of banking system\n- higher supply of bonds\n- bond prices fall, bond yields rise\n- rates rise",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "kVDe2oCuFDtG36WQ_-5BB",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 1532.5090422627943,
      "y": 1330.3080996660988,
      "width": 734.1328034327661,
      "height": 332.5209411303761,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#846358",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "P1vscvoACG5iCgGEnvgQz"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1T",
      "roundness": {
        "type": 3
      },
      "seed": 2057611396,
      "version": 2601,
      "versionNonce": 681300013,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776141472985,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false
    },
    {
      "id": "tFoNtdxi4i7gsA_uQnkJL",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1554.2684827325938,
      "y": 1350.0594325205611,
      "width": 710.3854845853263,
      "height": 258.73855870520333,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#846358",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "P1vscvoACG5iCgGEnvgQz"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1U",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 746911748,
      "version": 3382,
      "versionNonce": 778781325,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776141472985,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "B) Interest on Reserve Balances (IORB) and Overnight Reverse Repos (ON RRP)\n\nIORB = Commercial banks earn interest on reserve balances they already hold at the Fed\nON RRP = The Fed sells a bond and buys it back the next day with added interest.\nTypically sell to non-banks like Money Market Funds.\n\nDiscount Window rate  ←  ceiling  (banks borrow from Fed instead if EFFR exceeds this)\n        |\n    EFFR floats here\n        |\nIORB rate             ←  floor for banks\nON RRP rate           ←  floor for non-banks\n",
      "fontSize": 15.92237284339713,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "B) Interest on Reserve Balances (IORB) and Overnight Reverse Repos (ON RRP)\n\nIORB = Commercial banks earn interest on reserve balances they already hold at the Fed\nON RRP = The Fed sells a bond and buys it back the next day with added interest. Typically sell to non-banks like Money Market Funds.\n\nDiscount Window rate  ←  ceiling  (banks borrow from Fed instead if EFFR exceeds this)\n        |\n    EFFR floats here\n        |\nIORB rate             ←  floor for banks\nON RRP rate           ←  floor for non-banks\n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
